From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: peter <peter@navq.local>
Date: Thu, 26 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cmake: find LibLZMA in module mode

The cross-compile branch used find_package(LibLZMA HINTS ... REQUIRED).
Since CMake 4.3 the HINTS keyword forces Config mode, which looks for a
LibLZMAConfig.cmake that liblzma does not ship (it only provides pkg-config
and CMake's bundled FindLibLZMA module). Drop HINTS so module mode is used;
CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH already points at the recipe sysroot where liblzma is.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [cross-build/cmake-4.3 specific]
---
 src/CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/CMakeLists.txt b/src/CMakeLists.txt
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/src/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/src/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -45,7 +45,7 @@ if(NOT BUILD_WITHOUT_CURL)
     find_package(CURL REQUIRED)
 endif()
 if (CMAKE_CROSSCOMPILING)
-    find_package(LibLZMA HINTS "${CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH}" REQUIRED)
+    find_package(LibLZMA REQUIRED)
 else()
     find_package(LibLZMA REQUIRED)
 endif()
